<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="former-adj">former <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'fɔːmə(r)/    美 /'fɔːrmər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 以前的；从前的；前任的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is my former colleague. 
他是我以前的同事。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(两者中) 前面的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in the former case 
在前一种情况下</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Fish prefer shallow water to deep water because the former is warmer.
鱼喜欢浅水甚于深水，因为前者更暖和。</p><footer>2015广东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="the-formerthe-latter">the former...the latter</h3>
<p>1.<strong>前者......后者</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>formerly /'fɔːməli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Most of us, if we know even a little about where our food comes from, understand that every bite put into our mouth was <strong><em>_</em></strong> (former) alive.  （2015 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. formerly  </p></div>